1538→        <!-- Features (from baseline design-4379) -->
1539→        <section id="features" class="features">
1540→            <div class="grid-overlay"></div>
1541→            <div class="container">
1542→                <div class="section-header">
1543→                    <h2>Zero Knowledge. Zero Compromise.</h2>
1544→                    <p style="color: var(--text-light); max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto;">Your data never leaves your device unencrypted. We build privacy architecture, not data vacuums.</p>
1545→                </div>
1546→
1547→                <div class="feature-grid">
1548→                    <div class="feature-card">
1549→                        <div class="feature-icon">🔐</div>
1550→                        <h3>Pattern Encryption</h3>
1551→                        <p>Unlock with a geometric pattern. The pattern itself acts as the decryption key. No pattern, no data.</p>
1552→                    </div>
1553→
1554→                    <div class="feature-card">
1555→                        <div class="feature-icon">🎭</div>
1556→                        <h3>True Plausible Deniability</h3>
1557→                        <p>Every pattern opens up a vault. You can set up as many decoy vaults as you want.</p>
1558→                    </div>
1559→
1560→                    <div class="feature-card">
1561→                        <div class="feature-icon">🕶️</div>
1562→                        <h3>Hidden Vaults</h3>
1563→                        <p>Nobody can tell how many vaults exist on your device. Storage space is obfuscated to prevent analysis.</p>
1564→                    </div>
1565→
1566→                    <div class="feature-card">
1567→                        <div class="feature-icon">🚨</div>
1568→                        <h3>Duress Mode</h3>
1569→                        <p>Set a &ldquo;Duress Vault&rdquo; that when opened instantly deletes all other vaults without any notice.</p>
1570→                    </div>
1571→
1572→                    <div class="feature-card">
1573→                        <div class="feature-icon">☁️</div>
1574→                        <h3>Encrypted iCloud Backup</h3>
1575→                        <p>Optional off-site backup. Your data is encrypted locally <i>before</i> it ever touches Apple&rsquo;s servers.</p>
1576→                    </div>
1577→
1578→                    <div class="feature-card">
1579→                        <div class="feature-icon">🤝</div>
1580→                        <h3>Secure Sharing</h3>
1581→                        <p>Share vaults with others. Automatic synchronization, data export prevention, expiration and limit number of opens are all built in.</p>
1582→                    </div>
1583→                </div>
1584→            </div>
1585→        </section>
1586→
1587→        <!-- How It Works (from baseline design-4379) -->
1588→        <section id="how-it-works" class="timeline-section">
1589→            <div class="container">
1590→                <div class="section-header">
1591→                    <h2 style="color: var(--text-dark)">How It Works</h2>
1592→                </div>
1593→                <div class="timeline">
1594→                    <div class="step">
1595→                        <div class="step-marker"></div>
1596→                        <div class="step-number">01</div>
1597→                        <h3>Define Your Pattern</h3>
1598→                        <p>Draw a unique geometric pattern to generate a high-entropy encryption key.<br>The key is created directly on your device&rsquo;s Secure Enclave.</p>
1599→                    </div>
1600→                    <div class="step">
1601→                        <div class="step-marker"></div>
1602→                        <div class="step-number">02</div>
1603→                        <h3>Load the Vault</h3>
1604→                        <p>Import photos, documents, and notes. Files are instantly encrypted using AES-256 before being written to disk.</p>
1605→                    </div>
1606→                    <div class="step">
1607→                        <div class="step-marker"></div>
1608→                        <div class="step-number">03</div>
1609→                        <h3>Lock &amp; Vanish</h3>
1610→                        <p>Close the app. The decryption keys are wiped from memory. Without the pattern, your files look like random noise.</p>
1611→                    </div>
1612→                </div>
1613→            </div>
1614→        </section>
1615→
1616→        <!-- Security (from baseline design-4379) -->
1617→        <section id="security" class="security-section">
1618→            <div class="container">
1619→                <div class="tech-specs">
1620→                    <div class="tech-content">
1621→                        <h3>Security Architecture</h3>
1622→                        <p style="color: var(--accent-dark); font-size: 1.1rem;">We don&rsquo;t trust servers. We trust math.</p>
1623→                        <ul>
1624→                            <li><strong>AES-256-GCM</strong> file encryption</li>
1625→                            <li><strong>Argon2id</strong> key derivation</li>
1626→                            <li><strong>ChaCha20</strong> stream cipher for metadata</li>
1627→                            <li><strong>Zero-Knowledge</strong> architecture</li>
1628→                        </ul>
1629→                    </div>
1630→                    <div class="tech-diagram">
1631→                        <div class="code-block">
1632→                            <span class="code-key">const</span> vaultConfig = {<br>
1633→                            &nbsp;&nbsp;cipher: <span class="code-val">"AES-256-GCM"</span>,<br>
1634→                            &nbsp;&nbsp;kdf: <span class="code-val">"Argon2id"</span>,<br>
1635→                            &nbsp;&nbsp;iterations: <span class="code-val">128000</span>,<br>
1636→                            &nbsp;&nbsp;salt: <span class="code-val">unique_per_vault</span>,<br>
1637→                            &nbsp;&nbsp;cloud_sync: <span class="code-val">false</span> // default<br>
1638→                            };<br><br>
1639→                            <span style="color: var(--text-secondary)">// Server knows nothing.</span><br>
1640→                            <span style="color: var(--text-secondary)">// Only your pattern decrypts.</span>
1641→                        </div>
1642→                    </div>
1643→                </div>
1644→            </div>
1645→        </section>
1646→
1647→        <!-- FAQ (from baseline design-4379) -->
1648→        <section id="faq" class="faq-section">
1649→            <div class="container">
1650→                <div class="section-header">
1651→                    <h2 style="color: var(--text-dark)">Common Questions</h2>
1652→                </div>
1653→                <div class="faq-grid">
1654→                    <details class="faq-item">
1655→                        <summary class="faq-summary">What happens if I forget my pattern?</summary>
1656→                        <div class="faq-content">
1657→                            <p>You are provided with a secret passphrase that recovers the vault. However if your forget that too, the data is lost. We do not store keys or have a backdoor to the data.</p>
1658→                        </div>
1659→                    </details>
1660→                    <details class="faq-item">
1661→                        <summary class="faq-summary">Can Apple see my files?</summary>
1662→                        <div class="faq-content">
1663→                            <p>No. If you enable iCloud backup, we upload an encrypted blob. Apple hosts the file, but without your pattern key, it is mathematically impossible for them to read it.</p>
1664→                        </div>
1665→                    </details>
1666→                    <details class="faq-item">
1667→                        <summary class="faq-summary">Do I need an account?</summary>
1668→                        <div class="faq-content">
1669→                            <p>Absolutely not. Vaultaire works right out of the box. No email, no phone number, no signup.</p>
1670→                        </div>
1671→                    </details>
1672→                    <details class="faq-item">
1673→                        <summary class="faq-summary">Do you optimize my data?</summary>
1674→                        <div class="faq-content">
1675→                            <p>You have an option to store pictures and videos in optimized form, saving space and allowing for faster shares.</p>
1676→                        </div>
1677→                    </details>
1678→                    <details class="faq-item">
1679→                        <summary class="faq-summary">How does sharing work?</summary>
1680→                        <div class="faq-content">
1681→                            <p>When you share a vault you are provided with a secret phrase that differs from the vault recovery phrase. Recipient can use it to obtain copy of the data. You control how long they keep access or how many times they can open the vault. If you add files, the data is synchronized automatically.</p>
1682→                        </div>
1683→                    </details>
1684→                    <details class="faq-item">
1685→                        <summary class="faq-summary">Do you support folders?</summary>
1686→                        <div class="faq-content">
1687→                            <p>Not at this time. Instead we suggest you use different vaults to store different data.</p>
1688→                        </div>
1689→                    </details>
1690→                    <details class="faq-item">
1691→                        <summary class="faq-summary">What kind of data can I store?</summary>
1692→                        <div class="faq-content">
1693→                            <p>There is no limitation. Any file can be stored and shared.</p>
1694→                        </div>
1695→                    </details>
1696→                    <details class="faq-item">
1697→                        <summary class="faq-summary">How many vaults can I have?</summary>
1698→                        <div class="faq-content">
1699→                            <p>In the free version you are limited to 10 vaults. In paid it&rsquo;s unlimited.</p>
1700→                        </div>
1701→                    </details>
1702→                    <details class="faq-item">
1703→                        <summary class="faq-summary">How many files can I have per vault?</summary>
1704→                        <div class="faq-content">
1705→                            <p>There is no limit, however more files you add, bigger the vault and sharing becomes slower.</p>
1706→                        </div>
1707→                    </details>
1708→                    <details class="faq-item">
1709→                        <summary class="faq-summary">Do you collect any analytical data?</summary>
1710→                        <div class="faq-content">
1711→                            <p>If you give us permission (can be revoked at any time), we collect bugs, crashes and basic analytical information. There are no accounts, identity or any personal data attached. We have no idea who you are or what you are using Vaultaire for.</p>
1712→                        </div>
1713→                    </details>
1714→                </div>
1715→            </div>
1716→        </section>
1717→    </main>
